 {"id":"rust_proxy-btn","title":"Implement dry-run for stop command","description":"## Implement Dry-Run for Stop Command

### Overview

Add --dry-run support to the stop command so users can see what would happen without actually stopping the daemon.

### User Experience

```bash
$ rp stop --dry-run
Would stop daemon process (PID: 12345)
Would remove PID file at /var/run/rp.pid
Would close 3 active connections

No changes made (dry-run mode)

$ rp stop -n  # short flag
Would stop daemon process (PID: 12345)
...
```

### Implementation

```rust
pub async fn stop_command(args: StopArgs) -> Result<()> {
    let ctx = if args.dry_run {
        Some(DryRunContext::new())
    } else {
        None
    };

    // Check if daemon is running
    let pid = match read_pid_file() {
        Ok(pid) => pid,
        Err(_) => {
            if args.dry_run {
                println!("Daemon is not running. Nothing to do.");
            }
            return Ok(());
        }
    };

    if let Some(ref ctx) = ctx {
        ctx.would_do(&format!("Stop daemon process (PID: {})", pid));
        ctx.would_do(&format!("Remove PID file at {}", pid_file_path().display()));

        // Check for active connections if possible
        if let Ok(conn_count) = get_active_connection_count(pid) {
            if conn_count > 0 {
                ctx.would_do(&format!("Close {} active connection(s)", conn_count));
            }
        }

        println!("{}", ctx.format());
        println!("\nNo changes made (dry-run mode)");
        return Ok(());
    }

    // Actual stop logic
    stop_daemon(pid).await?;
    remove_pid_file()?;
    println!("Daemon stopped");
    Ok(())
}
```

### CLI Integration

```rust
#[derive(Parser)]
pub struct StopArgs {
    /// Show what would happen without actually stopping
    #[arg(short = 'n', long)]
    pub dry_run: bool,

    /// Output in JSON format
    #[arg(long)]
    pub json: bool,
}
```

### JSON Output

```json
{
  "dry_run": true,
  "actions": [
    "Stop daemon process (PID: 12345)",
    "Remove PID file at /var/run/rp.pid",
    "Close 3 active connections"
  ],
  "would_affect": {
    "pid": 12345,
    "pid_file": "/var/run/rp.pid",
    "active_connections": 3
  }
}
```

### Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] --dry-run flag available on stop command
- [ ] -n short form works
- [ ] Shows PID that would be stopped
- [ ] Shows PID file that would be removed
- [ ] Shows connection count if available
- [ ] Does NOT actually stop daemon
- [ ] JSON output format works","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","owner":"jeff141421@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-01-18T14:56:09.424952893-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone","updated_at":"2026-01-18T14:56:09.424952893-05:00","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"rust_proxy-btn","depends_on_id":"rust_proxy-ar9","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-18T15:03:44.717463424-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone"}]}
 {"id":"rust_proxy-c1u","title":"Unit tests for Load Balancing","description":"## Unit Tests for Load Balancing

### Test Coverage Areas

1. **Strategy Configuration Parsing**
   ```rust
   #[test]
   fn test_parse_load_balance_strategy() {
       assert_eq!(parse_strategy("single").unwrap(), Strategy::Single);
       assert_eq!(parse_strategy("round_robin").unwrap(), Strategy::RoundRobin);
       assert_eq!(parse_strategy("least_latency").unwrap(), Strategy::LeastLatency);
       assert_eq!(parse_strategy("weighted").unwrap(), Strategy::Weighted);
       assert!(parse_strategy("invalid").is_err());
   }
   ```

2. **Single Strategy (Default)**
   ```rust
   #[test]
   fn test_single_strategy_returns_active() {
       let lb = LoadBalancer::new(Strategy::Single, &proxies);
       let selected = lb.select(&health_status);
       assert_eq!(selected, Some("active-proxy"));
   }
   ```

3. **Round-Robin Strategy**
   ```rust
   #[test]
   fn test_round_robin_cycles() {
       let lb = LoadBalancer::new(Strategy::RoundRobin, &proxies);
       assert_eq!(lb.select(&healthy_all), Some("proxy-a"));
       assert_eq!(lb.select(&healthy_all), Some("proxy-b"));
       assert_eq!(lb.select(&healthy_all), Some("proxy-c"));
       assert_eq!(lb.select(&healthy_all), Some("proxy-a")); // cycles back
   }

   #[test]
   fn test_round_robin_skips_unhealthy() {
       let lb = LoadBalancer::new(Strategy::RoundRobin, &proxies);
       let health = health_status_with_unhealthy("proxy-b");
       assert_eq!(lb.select(&health), Some("proxy-a"));
       assert_eq!(lb.select(&health), Some("proxy-c")); // skips proxy-b
   }
   ```

4. **Least-Latency Strategy**
   ```rust
   #[test]
   fn test_least_latency_selects_fastest() {
       let lb = LoadBalancer::new(Strategy::LeastLatency, &proxies);
       let latencies = hashmap! {
           "proxy-a" => 100.0,
           "proxy-b" => 50.0,
           "proxy-c" => 150.0,
       };
       assert_eq!(lb.select_with_latency(&healthy_all, &latencies), Some("proxy-b"));
   }

   #[test]
   fn test_least_latency_skips_unhealthy_even_if_fastest() {
       let lb = LoadBalancer::new(Strategy::LeastLatency, &proxies);
       let latencies = hashmap! {
           "proxy-a" => 100.0,
           "proxy-b" => 10.0,  // fastest but unhealthy
           "proxy-c" => 150.0,
       };
       let health = health_status_with_unhealthy("proxy-b");
       assert_eq!(lb.select_with_latency(&health, &latencies), Some("proxy-a"));
   }
   ```

5. **Weighted Strategy**
   ```rust
   #[test]
   fn test_weighted_distribution() {
       let lb = LoadBalancer::new(Strategy::Weighted, &proxies);
       let weights = hashmap! {
           "proxy-a" => 70,
           "proxy-b" => 30,
       };
       let mut counts = HashMap::new();
       for _ in 0..1000 {
           let selected = lb.select_weighted(&healthy_all, &weights).unwrap();
           *counts.entry(selected).or_insert(0) += 1;
       }
       // Should be roughly 70/30 distribution
       assert!(counts["proxy-a"] > 600 && counts["proxy-a"] < 800);
       assert!(counts["proxy-b"] > 200 && counts["proxy-b"] < 400);
   }
   ```

6. **Edge Cases**
   ```rust
   #[test]
   fn test_no_healthy_proxies_returns_none() {
       let lb = LoadBalancer::new(Strategy::RoundRobin, &proxies);
       assert_eq!(lb.select(&all_unhealthy), None);
   }

   #[test]
   fn test_single_proxy_always_returns_it() {
       let lb = LoadBalancer::new(Strategy::RoundRobin, &single_proxy);
       assert_eq!(lb.select(&healthy), Some("only-proxy"));
       assert_eq!(lb.select(&healthy), Some("only-proxy"));
   }
   ```

### Thread Safety Tests
```rust
#[tokio::test]
async fn test_concurrent_round_robin() {
    let lb = Arc::new(LoadBalancer::new(Strategy::RoundRobin, &proxies));
    let handles: Vec<_> = (0..100).map(|_| {
        let lb = lb.clone();
        tokio::spawn(async move { lb.select(&healthy_all) })
    }).collect();

    let results: Vec<_> = futures::future::join_all(handles).await
        .into_iter().filter_map(|r| r.ok()).collect();

    // All proxies should be selected approximately equally
    let counts = count_occurrences(&results);
    for count in counts.values() {
        assert!(*count > 20 && *count < 50);
    }
}
```

